ATTACHMENT A
Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Garden Wind, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
GARDEN WIND, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Garden Wind, LLC ("Garden Wind") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Garden Wind generating facility ("Garden Wind Facility").
Garden Wind is a wind turbine generating facility located in Hardin County, Iowa. The Garden Wind Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by ITC Midwest, LLC and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Garden Wind's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Garden Wind Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Garden Wind's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Garden Wind shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $708,688.74. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $59,057.39.
